Flat file comma-seperated value(CSV) files. Each entity will be stored in one file and each line store a real *. Need to parse the file and read data from it. \u5728\u4e00\u4e2a\u6587\u4ef6\u91cc\u9762\u50a8\u5b58\u4e00\u4e2a\u5b9e\u4f53\u7684\u6570\u636e\uff0c\u5bf9\u4e8e\u4e00\u4e2a\u60f3\u8981\u7684\u64cd\u4f5c\uff0c\u5fc5\u987b\u7f16\u5199\u7279\u5b9a\u7684\u7a0b\u5e8f\u8fdb\u884c\u8bfb\u53d6 Issue with Flat File Data integrity(for the same data in different files, how to ensure they are the same,\u6570\u636e\u4e00\u81f4\u6027) Implementation(\u5bfb\u627e\u7279\u5b9a\u8bb0\u5f55\u9700\u8981\u91cd\u65b0\u7f16\u5199\u7a0b\u5e8f) Durability(\u6570\u636e\u5728crash\u65f6\u80fd\u5426\u4fdd\u5b58) 3. Database Management System A DBMS is a software that allows applications to store and analyze information in a database. A general-purpose DBMS allow the definision, creation, querying, update and administration of database in accordance with some data model. data model: a collection of concepts for describling the data in the database. schema: description of a particular collection of data based on a data model. 4. Relational Model The ralational model defines a database abstraction based on relations to avoid maintenance overhead key tenets: store databases in simple data structure physical storage left up to the DBMS implementation access data through high-level language A relation is an unordered set that contain the relationship of attributes that represent entities A tuple is a set of attribute values in the relation values are(normally) atomic/scalar(\u539f\u5b50\u6027\u7684\uff0c\u6bcf\u4e00\u4e2aattribute\u4e0d\u80fd\u62c6\u5206\u6210\u66f4\u5c0f\u7684\u6570\u636e\u5355\u5143) The special value NULL is a member of every domain Key: A relation's primary key uniquely identifies a single tuple. Foreign key: an attribute from one relation has to map to a tuple in another relation 5. Data Manipulation Language Procedural: \u8bf4\u660e\u5bfb\u627e\u6570\u636e\u7684\u7b97\u6cd5\u662f\u4ec0\u4e48 Non-Procedural: \u8bf4\u660e\u8981\u627e\u7684\u6570\u636e\u7684\u5c5e\u6027\uff0c\u5176\u4ed6\u7684\u4ea4\u7ed9DBMS 6. Relation ALgebra 6.1 select Choose a subset of tuples from a relation that satisfies a selection predicate. \u6839\u636e\u6761\u4ef6\u7b5b\u9009\u6ee1\u8db3\u6761\u4ef6\u7684tuple $\\sigma_{predicate}(R)$ 6.2 Projection Generate a relation with tuples that contains only the specified attibutes. \u53ea\u4fdd\u7559\u5f53\u524dtuples\u7684\u90e8\u5206\u5c5e\u6027 $\\pi_{A1,A2,...,An}(R)$ 6.3 Union Generate a relation that contains all tuple that appear in either one or both input relations","title":"Lec1 Relational Model and Relational Algebra"},{"location":"CMU15-445/Lec1%20Relational%20Model%20and%20Relational%20Algebra/#lec1-relational-model-and-relational-algebramd","text":"","title":"Lec1 Relational Model and Relational Algebra.md"},{"location":"CMU15-445/Lec1%20Relational%20Model%20and%20Relational%20Algebra/#1-databases","text":"organized huge mount of data that models some aspect of the real-world. DBMS is the software that trying to manage the databases. \u6570\u636e\u5e93\u5c31\u662f\u4e00\u5927\u5806\u9700\u8981\u7ba1\u7406\u7684\u6570\u636e\uff0c\u4ed6\u4eec\u4ee3\u8868\u4e86\u67d0\u79cd\u771f\u5b9e\u4e16\u754c\u7684\u7279\u5f81\uff0c\u5e76\u4e14\u5177\u6709\u5c5e\u6027\u4e0a\u7684\u76f8\u4f3c\u6027\u3002DBMS\u5c31\u662f\u7528\u6765\u7ba1\u7406\u8fd9\u4e9b\u6709\u5e8f\u7684\u6570\u636e\u7684\u8f6f\u4ef6\u3002 !!! note[]","title":"1. Databases"},{"location":"CMU15-445/Lec1%20Relational%20Model%20and%20Relational%20Algebra/#2-flat-file","text":"comma-seperated value(CSV) files. Each entity will be stored in one file and each line store a real *. Need to parse the file and read data from it. \u5728\u4e00\u4e2a\u6587\u4ef6\u91cc\u9762\u50a8\u5b58\u4e00\u4e2a\u5b9e\u4f53\u7684\u6570\u636e\uff0c\u5bf9\u4e8e\u4e00\u4e2a\u60f3\u8981\u7684\u64cd\u4f5c\uff0c\u5fc5\u987b\u7f16\u5199\u7279\u5b9a\u7684\u7a0b\u5e8f\u8fdb\u884c